title: The Art Institute of Chicago Facade Wood Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893 and main entrance, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The ornament is made from solid, sustainable Black Cherry wood, engraved and cut with intricate detail. Finished with a food safe oil, each piece comes with a ribbon for hanging. Made by Nestled Pines Woodworking, a company focused on combining design, nature, and sustainability with technology to create unique works of art.   Manufactured in the USA.

  • Dimensions:  4 x 2.75 x .2 in.
  • Materials:  Black Cherry Wood
